# Econumo configuration. Copy to .env and fill in:
#
#   cp .env.example .env
#
# This single template serves BOTH the docker compose stack (env_file: .env) and a
# host `go run` (the binary auto-loads ./.env; real environment variables always
# take precedence over it). Do NOT commit .env — it may hold secrets. .env is
# gitignored; this template is committed.

APP_ENV=prod

# Enable or disable user registration.
ECONUMO_ALLOW_REGISTRATION=true

# Password-recovery email via Resend (https://resend.com). Set the API key and a
# verified From address to enable it; leave the key empty to disable email.
# RESEND_API_KEY=re_xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
# ECONUMO_FROM_EMAIL=noreply@yourdomain.com
# ECONUMO_REPLY_TO_EMAIL=support@yourdomain.com

# Multi-currency support (https://econumo.com/docs/self-hosting/multi-currency/):
# ECONUMO_CURRENCY_BASE=USD
# OPEN_EXCHANGE_RATES_TOKEN=

# JWT keypair: auto-generated on first boot at var/jwt (in Docker: /app/var/jwt;
# persist the data volume to keep tokens valid). Optional overrides:
# JWT_PASSPHRASE=
# JWT_SECRET_KEY=var/jwt/private.pem
# JWT_PUBLIC_KEY=var/jwt/public.pem

# DEPRECATED (to be removed): email-at-rest salt. Leave unset for plaintext emails;
# migrate an existing salted DB with `app:remove-data-salt`. See CLAUDE.md.
# ECONUMO_DATA_SALT=

# Database DSN. In Docker the image sets this (sqlite:///app/var/db/db.sqlite) — leave
# it unset. For a bare `go run` set it explicitly (`make run` sets it for you).
# An absolute sqlite path needs the triple slash:
# DATABASE_URL=sqlite:///absolute/path/to/econumo/var/db/db.sqlite

# Listen port. In Docker the container always listens on 80 (map it in compose);
# `make run` uses 8181. Set only for a bare `go run`:
# PORT=8181
